# Build artifacts.
/assay
*.test
*.exe

# Dev/CI tool binaries built from tools.go.mod (golangci-lint,
# gotestsum, etc.). Built into ./bin/ by `just sync-tools` because
# the standard `go tool -modfile=tools.go.mod` invocation clashes
# with assay's committed vendor/ (Go enables vendor mode and the
# tool deps don't appear in vendor/modules.txt). Pre-building into
# bin/ sidesteps the clash; pin-by-tools.go.mod keeps versions
# reproducible.
/bin/

# Test artifacts.
/coverage.out
/profile.out

# Editor / OS.
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/

# vendor/ — TEMPORARILY COMMITTED.
#
# assay depends on sibling libraries (go-bzlmod, starlark-go-bazel)
# that aren't yet published with stable tags. go.mod uses relative-path
# `replace` directives to find them during local dev (`../sibling-name`),
# but those paths don't exist in a fresh clone or a stock CI checkout —
# `go build` would fail without committed vendor/. Vendoring closes the
# gap until the sibling libs ship real versions on the module proxy.
#
# When that day comes: uncomment the line below + run
# `git rm -r --cached vendor/` + drop the `replace` directives from
# go.mod + pin the `require` lines to real versions.
#
# /vendor/
